<pre class="bz_comment_text">(In reply to <a href="show_bug.cgi?id=678348#c1">comment #1</a>)
<span class="quote">&gt; There's a tentative patch for this in
&gt; <a href="http://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=678026">http://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=678026</a></span>

You should put the patch here, but a couple of problems:
- you're still hard-coding /tmp, that's not good
- g_dir_make_tmp() is a better option than mkdtemp()
- Fix max_addr_length to use an allocated string (eg. g_strdup_printf instead of sprintf) (not even snprintf!)</pre>
